body:
I am using a refinedmentList widget to filter my results based on type. I want each result to have a button with the type value they belong to. When the button is clicked I want to add a filter for the clicked facet type to the refinedmentList widget.

Here is my current code instantsearch.js setup code.

```js
const { algoliasearch, instantsearch } = window;

const searchClient = algoliasearch(
    'XXX',
    'XXX'
);

const search = instantsearch({
    indexName: 'XXX',
    searchClient,
});

search.addWidgets([
    instantsearch.widgets.searchBox({
        container: '#searchbox',
        autofocus: true
    }),
    instantsearch.widgets.hits({
        container: '#hits',
        templates: {
            item(hit, { html, components }) {
                return html`
                    <div>
                        <div class="hit-name"><a href="/${hit.id}">${components.Highlight({ hit, attribute: 'title' })}</a></div>
                        <div class="hit-description">${components.Snippet({ hit, attribute: 'text' })}</div>
                        <button class="type_button bg-red-400 hover:bg-red-600 text-white font-bold ml-1 py-1 px-4 border border-red-600 rounded" onclick="alert('This never fires because it does not end up on the actual button element');">${hit.type}</button>
                    </div>
                `;
            },
        },
    }),

    instantsearch.widgets.refinementList({
        container: '#type-list',
        attribute: 'type',
        showMore:true,
        showMoreLimit: 100,
    }),
]);

search.start();
```

Is there a way for me to do this?
